1.  **Weight Loss:** If you've lost a significant amount of weight in a short time, especially if you're feeling weak, dizzy, or cold, call the National Eating Disorders Helpline at (800) 931-2237 or text “NEDA” to 741741 for immediate support.

2.  **Dizziness:** If dizziness is occurring when low on food frequently, call the national Eating  Disorders helpline at (800) 931-2237 or text “NEDA” to 741741 for immediate help.&#x20;

3.  **Contact a doctor:** If you are fainting and you don't know why, consider contacting a doctor/physician so you can jumpstart treatment.&#x20;

4.  **Cutting calories is very dangerous and should never be attempted not even at the expense of correct substances.**
